<div class="jumbotron half-page">
	<div class="container">
		<p>It's {{now}}, do you know how risky your commits are?</p>
		<h1>
			<span class="fa fa-magic"></span> Ask the Commit Guru
		</h1>
		<p>View automatically generated reports of your repository's commits. Anywhere.</p>
	</div>
</div>
<div class="container">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-md-6">
			<h1>Analyze a Repository</h1>
			<form novalidate class="form-horizontal" role="form" name="quickAddForm" ng-submit="quickActions.quickAddRepo()">
				<div class="form-group" ng-class="{'has-error':quickAddForm.url.$dirty && quickAddForm.url.$invalid}">
					<label class="control-label col-sm-4" for="repo_url">Repository URL*</label>
					<div class="col-sm-8">
						<input required type="url" ng-model="quickActions.repo_url" class="form-control input-lg" id="repo_url" name="url">
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="form-group" ng-class="{'has-error':quickAddForm.email.$dirty && quickAddForm.email.$invalid}">
					<label class="control-label col-sm-4" for="repo_email">Email</label>
					<div class="col-sm-8">
						<input ng-model="quickActions.repo_email" type="email" class="form-control input-lg" id="repo_email" name="email">
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="form-group">
					<div class="col-sm-offset-4 col-sm-8">
						<div class="checkbox">
							<label><input type="checkbox" ng-model="quickActions.listed"> List publicly? (Always will be accessible directly)</label>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="form-group">
					<div class="col-sm-offset-4 col-sm-8">
						<button type="submit" ng-disabled="quickAddForm.$invalid" class="btn btn-success btn-lg">Start Now <i class="fa fa-angle-right"></i></button>
					</div>
				</div>
			</form>
		</div>
		<div class="col-md-6">
			<h1>Create an account</h1>
			<form novalidate class="form-horizontal" role="form" name="createUser" ng-submit="createUserFields.submit()">
				<div class="form-group" ng-class="{'has-error': createUser.email.$dirty && createUser.email.$invalid}">
					<label class="control-label col-sm-4" for="createUser_email">Email:</label>
					<div class="col-sm-8">
						<input required ng-model="createUserFields.email" type="email" class="form-control input-lg" id="createUser_email" name="email">
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="form-group" ng-class="{'has-error': createUser.password.$dirty && createUser.password.$invalid}">
					<label class="control-label col-sm-4" for="createUser_password">Password</label>
					<div class="col-sm-8">
						<input required type="password" ng-model="createUserFields.password" class="form-control input-lg" ng-minlength="6" id="createUser_password" name="password">
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="form-group">
					<div class="col-sm-offset-4 col-sm-8">
						<button type="submit" ng-disabled="createUser.$invalid" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg"><i class="fa fa-user"></i> Sign Up</button>
					</div>
				</div>
			</form>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-md-6">
			<h1>Recent Repositories</h1>
			<div class="list-group">
				<a href="/repo/{{item.name}}" class="list-group-item" ng-repeat="item in items">
					<h4 class="list-group-item-heading">{{item.name}}</h4>
					<p class="list-group-item-text">
						<span ng-if="item.ingestion_date.length > 0">Last Ingested: {{item.ingestion_date}}</span><span ng-if="item.analysis_date.length > 0">, Last Analyzed: {{item.analysis_date}}</span>
					</p>
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="col-md-6">
			<h1>How it Works:</h1>
			<div class="center">
				<p class="lead"><i class="fa fa-download fa-5x"></i><br><br>First, we pull your repository to our servers</p>
				<p class="lead"><i class="fa fa-refresh fa-5x"></i><br><br>Next, we analyze your commits every day</p>
				<p class="lead"><i class="fa fa-bar-chart-o fa-5x"></i><br><br>Finally, we display the results online</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	</div>
</div>